        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 8:41PM EDT by NWS Gaylord MI</headline>
        <description>At 840 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Curran, or 8 miles southwest of The Town Of
Hubbard Lake, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Spruce, Barton City, Hubbard Lake, Curran, and Lost Lake Woods.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
